('grammar','multiple_choice','The flight _____ delayed because the catering truck broke down.\nA) is\nB) was\nC) were\nD) been','B','A2','easy','tense_usage','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('grammar','multiple_choice','How _____ containers are we loading on this flight?\nA) many\nB) much\nC) some\nD) any','A','A2','easy','structural_accuracy','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('grammar','multiple_choice','The dispatcher confirmed that the load sheet _____ correct.\nA) is\nB) was\nC) were\nD) are','B','B1','medium','tense_usage','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('grammar','fill_blank','Complete: The de-icing was performed _____ (thorough) before takeoff.','thoroughly','B1','medium','structural_accuracy','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('grammar','multiple_choice','Each container _____ a maximum weight limit that must not be exceeded.\nA) has\nB) have\nC) having\nD) had','A','A2','easy','structural_accuracy','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('grammar','multiple_choice','The ground coordinator asked _____ the aircraft would arrive on time.\nA) that\nB) if\nC) what\nD) which','B','B1','medium','structural_accuracy','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('grammar','multiple_choice','We _____ just finished loading when the captain requested a weight change.\nA) had\nB) have\nC) has\nD) were','A','B1','medium','tense_usage','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('grammar','multiple_choice','Dangerous goods _____ be declared and properly labelled before loading.\nA) must\nB) can\nC) might\nD) should','A','B1','medium','phraseology_grammar','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),

-- Reading (10)
('reading','multiple_choice','Read the ramp safety sign:\n\n"WARNING: Jet blast zone — Stay clear of area behind running engines. Minimum safe distance: 60 metres for narrow-body, 100 metres for wide-body aircraft. Failure to maintain safe distance may result in serious injury or death."\n\nWhat is the safe distance from a wide-body engine?\nA) 30 metres\nB) 60 metres\nC) 100 metres\nD) 200 metres','C','A2','easy','safety_card_reading','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('reading','multiple_choice','Read the load instruction:\n\n"ULD Loading Sequence for TC-FLY (B737-800):\nForward hold: Positions 1-2: Bulk baggage. Position 3: Priority/fragile.\nAft hold: Positions 4-5: Standard baggage. Position 6: Mail/cargo.\nMaximum forward hold: 3,200 kg. Maximum aft hold: 4,500 kg."\n\nWhere should fragile items be loaded?\nA) Position 1\nB) Position 3\nC) Position 5\nD) Position 6','B','B1','medium','sop_comprehension','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('reading','multiple_choice','Read the dangerous goods label:\n\n"UN3481 — Lithium Ion Batteries packed with equipment. Class 9 Miscellaneous Dangerous Goods. Maximum: 5kg per package. Must be in original packaging. Keep upright. Do NOT load near heat sources or in pressurized cargo compartments above 25°C."\n\nWhat class of dangerous goods is this?\nA) Class 1 — Explosives\nB) Class 3 — Flammable liquid\nC) Class 9 — Miscellaneous\nD) Class 7 — Radioactive','C','B1','medium','technical_manual','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('reading','multiple_choice','Read the winter operations bulletin:\n\n"DE-ICING PROCEDURES: Type I fluid: heated — removes existing contamination. Type IV fluid: unheated — provides anti-icing protection. Holdover time for Type IV in moderate snow: 15-25 minutes. Aircraft must depart within holdover time or de-icing must be repeated."\n\nWhat happens if holdover time expires?\nA) Aircraft can still depart\nB) De-icing must be repeated\nC) Only Type I is reapplied\nD) The flight is cancelled','B','B1','medium','technical_manual','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('reading','multiple_choice','Read the turnaround schedule:\n\n"Target turnaround: 35 minutes\n0:00 — Aircraft on blocks, doors open\n0:05 — Catering, cleaning, fueling begin\n0:15 — Baggage offload complete\n0:20 — Boarding begins\n0:30 — Doors close, pushback clearance requested\n0:35 — Off blocks"\n\nWhen does boarding begin?\nA) At 0:05\nB) At 0:15\nC) At 0:20\nD) At 0:30','C','A2','easy','sop_comprehension','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('reading','multiple_choice','Read the vehicle safety rule:\n\n"All ramp vehicles must: 1) Have working lights and horn 2) Display valid inspection sticker 3) Not exceed 25 km/h (15 km/h near aircraft) 4) Give way to aircraft at all times 5) Not pass under aircraft wings or fuselage 6) Maintain 3-metre clearance from all aircraft."\n\nWhat is the speed limit near aircraft?\nA) 25 km/h\nB) 15 km/h\nC) 10 km/h\nD) 5 km/h','B','A2','easy','safety_card_reading','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('reading','multiple_choice','Read the load message:\n\n"LDM TC-FLY/18MAR\nPAX: 168/3/12 (M/F/CHD) + 2 INF\nBAG: 183 PCS / 2,745 KG\nCARGO: 450 KG (FWD), 320 KG (AFT)\nMAIL: 85 KG (AFT)\nTOTAL PAYLOAD: 14,320 KG\nMAX PAYLOAD: 16,200 KG"\n\nHow much additional payload capacity is available?\nA) 1,880 kg\nB) 2,745 kg\nC) 14,320 kg\nD) 450 kg','A','B2','hard','technical_manual','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('reading','multiple_choice','Read the FOD prevention policy:\n\n"All ground staff must perform a FOD walk of their assigned stand before and after each aircraft arrival/departure. Report findings on the daily FOD log. Any metal debris, loose bolts, or foreign objects must be collected immediately. FOD bins are located at each gate."\n\nWhen must FOD walks be performed?\nA) Only before arrivals\nB) Before and after each arrival/departure\nC) Once per day\nD) Only when requested','B','A2','easy','sop_comprehension','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('reading','multiple_choice','Read the communication protocol:\n\n"Headset Communication with Flight Deck:\n- Always identify yourself: ''Ground to flight deck''\n- Confirm pushback clearance: ''Cleared to push, facing [direction]''\n- Report brakes: ''Brakes set/released''\n- Disconnect: ''Cleared to start, disconnecting, have a safe flight''\n- NEVER walk under aircraft without headset connected"\n\nWhat must you say before disconnecting?\nA) Goodbye\nB) Cleared to start, disconnecting, have a safe flight\nC) Pushback complete\nD) Thank you','B','B1','medium','sop_comprehension','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('reading','multiple_choice','Read the weight restriction:\n\n"MANUAL HANDLING LIMITS:\n- One person: Maximum 23 kg\n- Two persons: Maximum 40 kg\n- Bags over 32 kg: Must use belt loader/mechanical lift\n- Oversized items (ski, wheelchair): Must be loaded last, removed first\nTeam lifting training must be completed annually."\n\nWhat is the max weight one person can lift?\nA) 15 kg\nB) 23 kg\nC) 32 kg\nD) 40 kg','B','A2','easy','safety_card_reading','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),

-- Writing (8)
('writing','written_response','A passenger''s suitcase was damaged during loading — the handle is broken and there is a large tear. Write a damage report (at least 50 words) including the flight, description of damage, and what you recommend.','Model answer should include flight number, bag tag, damage description, cause if known, compensation recommendation.','A2','easy','incident_report','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('writing','written_response','Write a shift handover note (at least 50 words) for the next ground crew shift. Include completed flights, pending tasks, equipment issues, and weather conditions.','Model answer should include completed turnarounds, pending departures, broken equipment, weather advisory.','B1','medium','operational_message','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('writing','written_response','A vehicle incident occurred on the ramp — a baggage tractor hit a cone and nearly struck an aircraft nose wheel. Write a safety report (at least 60 words) describing the incident and recommending preventive measures.','Model answer should include time, location, vehicle ID, driver, near-miss details, recommendations.','B1','medium','safety_report','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('writing','written_response','Write an email (at least 50 words) to the operations manager requesting new high-visibility vests for your team. The current ones are faded and no longer meet safety standards.','Model answer should include specific need, quantity, current condition, safety standard reference, urgency.','A2','easy','operational_message','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('writing','written_response','A flight has been overbooked and 5 passengers need to be offloaded. Write the announcement (at least 50 words) that would be made at the gate, offering compensation for volunteers.','Model answer should include professional tone, compensation offer, rebooking details, volunteer request.','B1','medium','cabin_announcement','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('writing','written_response','Write a brief procedure description (at least 50 words) explaining the correct pushback sequence from a terminal gate, including who communicates with whom.','Model answer should include chock removal, headset connection, clearance from tower, brake release, pushback direction.','B1','medium','technical_description','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('writing','written_response','You noticed that the de-icing fluid at your station has expired (past the batch expiry date on the label). Write a report (at least 50 words) to your supervisor about this issue.','Model answer should include fluid type, batch number, expiry date, location, safety concern, recommendation to replace.','B1','medium','safety_report','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('writing','written_response','Write a passenger complaint response (at least 60 words) for a traveler whose wheelchair was not at the aircraft door when they landed, causing them to wait 25 minutes on the jetbridge.','Model answer should include apology, acknowledge inconvenience, explain likely cause, corrective action, compensation if applicable.','B2','medium','passenger_complaint','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),

-- Speaking (8)
('speaking','audio_response','You are a marshaller guiding an aircraft to its parking stand. Describe the hand signals you would use and what each means.\n\nSpeak for at least 30 seconds.','Expected: Description of common signals — this way, slow down, stop, cut engines, chocks in. Clear explanation.','A2','easy','oral_briefing','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('speaking','audio_response','Roleplay: You are on the headset communicating with the flight deck during pushback. Walk through the complete pushback sequence from start to disconnect.\n\nSpeak for at least 40 seconds.','Expected: Ground to flight deck identification, clearance confirmed, brakes released, pushback direction, stop, cleared to start, disconnect.','B1','medium','ground_communication','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('speaking','audio_response','Explain the dangers of working near aircraft engines. What areas are dangerous and what precautions must be taken?\n\nSpeak for at least 30 seconds.','Expected: Intake danger zone, jet blast zone, distances, hearing protection, awareness of engine status.','A2','easy','oral_briefing','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('speaking','audio_response','A flight is delayed by 90 minutes and passengers at the gate are getting frustrated. How would you handle the situation? What would you say to them?\n\nSpeak for at least 40 seconds.','Expected: Empathetic communication, honest information, refreshment offer, rebooking assistance, calm demeanor.','B1','medium','roleplay_passenger','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('speaking','audio_response','Describe the de-icing process for an aircraft. What types of fluid are used and why is it important?\n\nSpeak for at least 40 seconds.','Expected: Type I and IV fluid, removal vs protection, holdover time, safety importance, when required.','B2','medium','oral_briefing','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('speaking','audio_response','You discovered a fuel spill near Gate 7. Describe what immediate actions you would take.\n\nSpeak for at least 30 seconds.','Expected: Alert others, cordon off area, notify fire services, prevent ignition sources, report to supervisor, spill kit.','A2','easy','roleplay_emergency','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('speaking','audio_response','Explain what a Load and Balance sheet is, why it is critical, and what can happen if an aircraft is loaded incorrectly.\n\nSpeak for at least 40 seconds.','Expected: Weight distribution, CG importance, safety implications, examples of incorrect loading consequences.','B2','hard','oral_briefing','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('speaking','audio_response','Roleplay: A passenger at the gate tells you their bag is too heavy and asks you to help them rearrange items between two bags. How would you assist while following safety rules?\n\nSpeak for at least 30 seconds.','Expected: Helpful attitude, weight limits explanation, offer assistance, security awareness.','A2','easy','roleplay_passenger','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),

-- Listening (12)
('listening','multiple_choice','[AUDIO] "Ramp Control, this is Gate 12. The aircraft has arrived on blocks. Requesting permission to approach for chock placement and ground power connection."\n\nWhat is being requested?\nA) Permission to fuel the aircraft\nB) Permission to approach for chocks and ground power\nC) Permission to board passengers\nD) Permission to push back','B','A2','easy','ground_ops_radio','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('listening','multiple_choice','[AUDIO] "Attention all ground staff: Wind is now gusting to 45 knots. All loose equipment must be secured immediately. Suspend loading operations on open stands until wind drops below 35 knots. Container loading may continue in sheltered positions only."\n\nAt what wind speed can loading resume on open stands?\nA) 45 knots\nB) Below 35 knots\nC) 25 knots\nD) Loading is permanently stopped','B','B1','medium','emergency_broadcast','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('listening','multiple_choice','[AUDIO] "Dispatcher to Ground 7: Flight TK2040 has a last-minute cargo addition — 320 kg of pharmaceutical goods, temperature sensitive, must go in the heated forward hold. Please confirm you can accommodate."\n\nWhere must the cargo be loaded?\nA) Aft hold\nB) Heated forward hold\nC) Bulk cargo area\nD) Passenger cabin','B','B1','medium','ground_ops_radio','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('listening','multiple_choice','[AUDIO] "This is the ramp supervisor. I need all teams to do a complete FOD walk of Stands 1 through 8 before the next wave of arrivals. That is in 20 minutes. Report findings on Channel 3."\n\nHow much time before the arrivals?\nA) 10 minutes\nB) 20 minutes\nC) 30 minutes\nD) 1 hour','B','A2','easy','ground_ops_radio','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('listening','multiple_choice','[AUDIO] "Ground crew at Stand 14, be advised: the aircraft arriving is a wide-body A330. You currently have narrow-body equipment staged. Please swap to wide-body bridge adaptor, belt loader, and tow bar before arrival in 15 minutes."\n\nWhat needs to change?\nA) The gate number\nB) Equipment must be swapped to wide-body\nC) The arrival time\nD) The crew assignment','B','B1','medium','ground_ops_radio','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('listening','multiple_choice','[AUDIO] "Security alert: An unattended bag has been found at Gate 22 boarding area. All ground operations at Gate 22 are suspended. Do not touch the bag. Security team is en route. Clear the area within 30 metres."\n\nWhat should you NOT do?\nA) Clear the area\nB) Touch the bag\nC) Wait for security\nD) Report to supervisor','B','A2','easy','emergency_broadcast','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('listening','multiple_choice','[AUDIO] "Load Control to Gate 5: Updated load instruction — move 2 bags from Position 4 aft to Position 2 forward. This is for CG adjustment. The captain requires revised trim before departure. Confirm when done."\n\nWhy are bags being moved?\nA) They are overweight\nB) For centre of gravity adjustment\nC) They are on the wrong flight\nD) The aft hold is full','B','B1','medium','ground_ops_radio','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('listening','multiple_choice','[AUDIO] "Fueling operator to Ground Control: Fueling of TC-FLY at Stand 9 is complete. Total uplift: 14,200 litres of Jet A-1. Fuel caps secured. Fueling equipment disconnecting now. Ground crew may resume operations around the aircraft."\n\nHow much fuel was loaded?\nA) 9,000 litres\nB) 12,000 litres\nC) 14,200 litres\nD) 16,000 litres','C','A2','easy','ground_ops_radio','fuel_system','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('listening','multiple_choice','[AUDIO] "Ramp supervisor to all teams: We have a medical emergency on the arriving flight at Gate 3. Ambulance is on the way. Please ensure the path from Gate 3 to the ambulance access point via Service Road B is completely clear. No vehicles in that area."\n\nWhat must be cleared?\nA) The runway\nB) The path from Gate 3 to ambulance access on Service Road B\nC) All gates\nD) The terminal building','B','B1','medium','emergency_broadcast','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('listening','multiple_choice','[AUDIO] "Ground to Flight Deck, TC-FLY. Pushback is approved by ATC, facing south. Confirm brakes released."\n"Brakes released, cleared to push."\n"Pushing back, facing south. Standby for start clearance."\n\nWhich direction is the aircraft being pushed?\nA) North\nB) South\nC) East\nD) West','B','A2','easy','ground_ops_radio','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('listening','multiple_choice','[AUDIO] "Attention: Ice and snow removal team to Taxiway Bravo between B2 and B6. Braking action reported poor by the last arrival. Airport operations has requested immediate treatment. Use glycol-based de-icer. Coordinate with Tower before entering taxiway."\n\nWhat is the braking condition?\nA) Good\nB) Medium\nC) Poor\nD) Not reported','C','B1','medium','ground_ops_radio','general','ground_staff',true,true,1),
('listening','multiple_choice','[AUDIO] "Hi, I am from the catering company. I have 12 trolleys for flight TK2090 at Gate 8. But the aircraft door L2 is not open yet. Can someone open it? We are running behind schedule and the flight departs in 40 minutes."\n\nWhat is the catering company''s problem?\nA) Wrong gate\nB) Aircraft door L2 is not open\nC) Not enough trolleys\nD) The flight is cancelled','B','A2','easy','ground_ops_radio','general','ground_staff',true,true,1);


-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- VERIFICATION QUERY
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
SELECT role_tag, section, count(*) as question_count
FROM questions 
WHERE active = true AND is_latest = true
GROUP BY role_tag, section
ORDER BY role_tag, section;
